Formulate an allocation scheme that maximizes the number of successfully matched patient–treatment room pairs while satisfying all stated constraints.

A cloud computing cluster is optimizing the assignment logic of its central task scheduler. The facility comprises seven incoming computational tasks (indexed 0 to 6) and five servers equipped with specific hardware accelerators (indexed 0 to 4). Due to constraints imposed by software dependencies and hardware compatibility, not every computational task can be executed on every server. There are exactly 15 predefined feasible compatibility paths, specified as follows:
- Incoming computational task 0 can connect to server 3 or server 4;
- Incoming computational task 1 can connect to server 0, server 3, or server 4;
- Incoming computational task 2 can connect to server 0 or server 3;
- Incoming computational task 3 can connect to server 1 or server 2;
- Incoming computational task 4 can connect to server 0 or server 1;
